<img width="1200" height="660" class="wp-image-1297008" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO.jpg" alt="6 states' NECO results withheld over 3-year examination fees debt" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO.jpg?width=1200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1200w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-300x165.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-1024x563.jpg?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-768x422.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-58x32.jpg?width=58&amp;auto_optimize=medium 58w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-260x143.jpg?width=260&amp;auto_optimize=medium 260w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-200x110.jpg?width=200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 200w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/NECO-560x308.jpg?width=560&amp;auto_optimize=medium 560w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /> By Joseph Erunke, Abuja THE National Examinations Council,NECO, has extended the registration period of the 2022 Senior School Certificate Examination,SSCE, for school based candidates to midnight of Monday 20th June, 2022. The registration period was initially scheduled to close on Monday 30th May, 2022. To this effect,the examination body in a statement, Monday morning by itsHead, Information and Public Relations Division,Azeez Sani,said:”State ministries of education, principals, commandants and all stakeholders are enjoined to note that there would be no further extension after that.” “The 2022 NECO Senior School Certificate Examination (SSCE) will commence on 27th June, 2022 and end on Friday 12th August, 2022.candidates are to be examined in 76 subjects during the examination,” the statement said.